The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, September 25, 2002 				 Lanka Muslims to ease Tamil rift
																								Colombo, Sept. 24 (Reuters): Sri Lankas top Muslim minister said today he would meet the head of the Tamil Tiger rebels to redress ethnic cleansing problems that had split the two communities and overshadowed talks to end the islands civil war.																								Muslim affairs minister Rauff Hakeem said he would meet Velupillai Prabhakaran soon to ease fears of Muslims that they would be left out of the peace talks in neutral Thailand.																								We can minimise our differences by bilateral discussions and make the main deliberations less complicated, he said. 
